The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Vallecito had a population of 442. The population density was {{convert|211.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Vallecito was 380 (86.0%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (0.7%) [[African Americans|African American]], 10 (2.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (0.5%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 12 (2.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 34 (7.7%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 31 persons (7.0%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Vallecito CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0681652 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 16, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 167 households, out of which 28 (16.8%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 92 (55.1%) were married-couple households, 9 (5.4%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 31 (18.6%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 35 (21.0%) had a male householder with no partner present. 38 households (22.8%) were one person, and 26 (15.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.65.<ref name=DP1/> There were 114 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (68.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Vallecito CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0681652 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 16, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 100 people (22.6%) under the age of 18, 27 people (6.1%) aged 18 to 24, 97 people (21.9%) aged 25 to 44, 106 people (24.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 112 people (25.3%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 44.6{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 116.7 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 191 housing units at an average density of {{convert|91.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 167 (87.4%) were occupied. Of these, 126 (75.4%) were owner-occupied, and 41 (24.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

